This paper deals with the study of behavioral metrics in a coalgebraic setting, which is a topic that is relevant to several areas of computer science. The paper uses tools from category theory and topology, which are commonly used in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the lifting of functors to pseudometric spaces, which is a topic that is relevant to the areas of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the modeling of linear-time metrics, which is a topic that is relevant to the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
